{
  "stem": "22856.1",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "In the beginning it was open, but later on, they closed it.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I can't forget the date when the ghetto was closed.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It was the 21st of March, 1941.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We were not allowed to live in the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We were lived outside the ghetto, but we had to come to the rabbi and to the ghetto to be married, to get the certificate, and later on we had to go back outside Cracow.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We were first in our normal apartments in Cracow, but then we had to rent some outside Cracow in some suburbs, I would say, not very far because we wanted to keep contact with our workplace.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But later on, when they closed the ghetto, there were only commandos surrounded by Ukrainian or German soldiers.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We went to work, and in the same way, they accompanied us when we wanted to come back home.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We were not allowed to-- because we had our armband with a David's star-- we can't-- in the beginning, we were not allowed to even to go to public restaurants, or we didn't-- we couldn't use public transport.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] The life became, from day to day, more and more difficult.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I was working in the private firm that was a general representation of Omega and Tissot watches.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And before the war broke out, we worked in big cities only, and they were also travelers for smaller areas.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But later on, when the Germany occupied Poland, all our traveling stopped.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We could only work in the office.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I worked in the office about 23, 25 people, a mixture of Jewish and non-Jewish.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Of course, majority was Jewish.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "There were groups that had permits, but only-- there were also single people who received for some purpose.",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
